Example
              * The following command specifies to calculate current  waveform
                using the rms, avg, and peak methods, and save violations in a
                report named sigem.rpt

                set_signal_em_analysis_mode \

                -method {rms avg peak} \

                -detailed true \

                -report sigem.rpt \

                -avgRecovery 0  \

                -useQrcTech true \

                -ict_em_models /../ictfile.ict \

                -em_threshold 0 \

                verify_AC_limit

              * The following is an example of the -extraction_tech_file para-
                meter:

                set_signal_em_analysis_mode -method {avg rms peak} -detailed \

                -ict_em_models ../../EMdata.ict \

                -extraction_tech_file qrc_file-em_temperature 105 \

                -avgRecovery 0.5 -report AC_signalEM.tcf.rpt -error 100000000

              * The  following  command specifies different temperature values
                to the layers M1, M2, M3, VIA1, VIA2,  and  VIA3  for  average
                current limit analysis:

                set_signal_em_analysis_mode

                   -em_temperature 110 \ #temperature for the remaining layers

                   -em_temperature_layer_list  {M1  125 M2 115 M3 105 VIA1 115
                VIA2 105 VIA3 120} #layer-based temperature

                The log file will display the following info message:

                Layer
                 specific EM temperature will be used for AVG check for  layer
                M1(125C),    M2(115C),   M3(105C),   VIA1(115C),   VIA2(105C),
                VIA3(120C).

